img_Facts.title: Francis Crick sculpture - geograph.org.uk - 1411215
img_Facts.caption: Francis Crick sculpture - geograph.org.uk - 1411215 Francis Crick sculpture This sculpture, erected in December 2005, is dedicated to Francis Crick who was born in Weston Favell, Northampton and is viewed as one of the greatest British scientists of the 20th century. He was awarded the Nobel Prize in 1962 and the Order of Merit in 1991.
img_Facts.detailed_caption: The Francis Crick sculpture, located in Weston Favell, Northampton, is a prominent feature in the image. The sculpture is set against a clear blue sky, which enhances its visibility and prominence. The surrounding area appears to be an open space, possibly a public square or park, with no other notable architectural structures or people visible in the immediate vicinity. The sculpture's design is sleek and contemporary, reflecting the scientific and intellectual legacy of Francis Crick.
